Upper Canada (Central Ontario) Marriage Indexes

The following databases have been recorded from marriage registers dating from the early 1800's for Upper Canada (Central Ontario.) Marriages from York County, Durham County, Peel County, Simcoe County, Northumberland County, Prince Edward County, Victoria County, Peterborough County, Haliburton County, Muskoka County, Hastings County and 'Old' Ontario County have been indexed. A number of 'outliers' ie. individuals from outside these areas may also be included. It is quite evident that by the 1840's numerous individuals were leaving the vicinity of the family farm for the growing opportunities that larger towns presented. You will find many individuals from the 'backwoods' of Ontario who were married in Toronto. Each record in my index consists of the surname and first name of the bride and groom, and year of marriage

The COMPLETE marriage record contains in most cases the names of the bride and groom, location or residence when married, names of witnesses, name of priest or minister officiating, and the date of marriage. Parents names are given in most Roman Catholic marriages, and also in some Anglican Church registrations.

There are errors in the database. In some cases the handwrighting or knowledge of the officials is to blame, names must sometimes be approximated or simply a 'best guess.' In other cases deterioration of the original record can prove to make interpretation of names tough. I have used local directories of the time period to try and sort out many of these records. In any case I accept no responsibility for the complete 'accuracy' of this database, but I will gladly use any information you can provide to 'fix' database errors.
